                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-09T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >September 9, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 9—8:42 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>439. Following from Shanghai: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 8, 4 p.m. My September 6, 11 a.m. repeating Tokyo’s 577,
                            September 5, 3 p.m. regarding Hankow safety zone.</p>
                        <p>The British and French Ambassadors are considering what action they will
                            take with reference to this matter and the latter has expressed a desire
                            to have your views on the subject. He desires especially to know whether
                            you have made any representations on the subject to the Chinese
                            authorities or whether you intend to make such representations. I have
                            communicated orally to the French Ambassador the substance of Hankow’s
                            September 7, 3 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d267fn88">Not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>I shall be glad to communicate to the French Ambassador any comments you
                            may care to make on the above subject.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
